# Mcd Card

## Summary
The `Mcd` card is a custom card definition that can be used within a Boxel application. It provides a reusable card component with specific functionality and data requirements.

## Import
To use the `Mcd` card in your Boxel application, import it from the specified module:

```javascript
import { Mcd } from '../mcd';
```

## Usage as a Field
The `Mcd` card can be used as a field within a consuming card or field definition. To use it, simply include it as a field in the `fields` section of your card or field definition:

```javascript
import { CardDef } from '@cardstack/core/card-api';

export default class MyCard extends CardDef {
  fields = {
    mcdField: { type: Mcd }
  };
}
```

## Template Usage
Within the template of the consuming card or field, you can display the `Mcd` card by using the field name you defined:

```handlebars
<div class="my-card">
  <h2>My Card</h2>
  {{mcdField}}
</div>
```

This will render the `Mcd` card inline within the consuming card or field.
